(112, 8, '2016-08-29 22:56:12', '2016-08-29 22:56:12', '[spb_row wrap_type=\"thin-width\" row_bg_type=\"color\" color_row_height=\"content-height\" bg_type=\"cover\" parallax_image_height=\"content-height\" parallax_image_movement=\"fixed\" parallax_image_speed=\"0.5\" parallax_video_height=\"window-height\" row_top_style=\"none\" row_bottom_style=\"none\" parallax_video_overlay=\"none\" row_overlay_opacity=\"0\" row_padding_vertical=\"70\" row_padding_horizontal=\"0\" row_margin_vertical=\"0\" remove_element_spacing=\"no\" inner_column_height=\"col-natural\" row_animation=\"none\" row_animation_delay=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [spb_text_block title=\"About Know Your Florida School\" animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"][/spb_text_block] [spb_accordion width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"1. What is Know Your Florida School?\" accordion_id=\"1--what-is-know-your-florida-school--\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nKnow Your Florida School is a prototype for the national Know Your School Project, an effort to help states promote parent access to useful school performance data.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"2. Where does the data come from?\" accordion_id=\"2--where-does-the-data-come-from-\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe data shown on Know Your Florida School comes from the Florida Department of Education’s Florida School Grades website. To view files directly from the Department, visit <a href=\"http://schoolgrades.fldoe.org/\">schoolgrades.fldoe.org</a>.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"3. What can parents do with the tool?\" accordion_id=\"3--what-can-parents-do-with-the-tool-\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nParents can use Know Your Florida School to find important information about their child’s school, specifically how students are performing academically. Parents can compare their school to others in the state and learn about ways to applaud success and support areas in need of improvement.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"4. Can parents engage with school leaders through the website? \" accordion_id=\"4--can-parents-engage-with-school-leaders-through-the-website---\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nKnow Your Florida School offers suggestions to parents on ways they can engage with school staff based on the student performance data,  displays the principals name, phone number, and links to the school website.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"5. What data does Know Your Florida School include?\" accordion_id=\"5--what-data-does-know-your-florida-school-include-\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nKnow Your Florida School provides comprehensive, accessible data from the 2014/15 and 2015/16 school years for Florida’s 3,300 public schools that earned a school grade. The prototype tool unpacks the components of each school’s grade and student performance, highlighting how a school compares to others in the state, and how it has performed over time. The tool clearly explains schools’ student performance (achievement), student progress (learning gains), graduation rates, and college and career readiness. Know Your Florida School also displays data depicting the school’s student population and characteristics.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"6. Will additional data or other school information be added to Know Your Florida School?\" accordion_id=\"6--will-additional-data-or-other-school-information-be-added-to-know-your-florida-school--\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe tool is designed to be expanded over time to include additional data indicators that impact student success, particularly the data required by the recently passed federal law, the Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA). Additional data will be added dependent upon availability and priority as identified by users of the tool.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"7. Why isn’t my school listed?\" accordion_id=\"7--why-isn-t-my-school-listed-\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe Florida Department of Education (FDOE) issues school grades annually for eligible K-12 public schools, including charter schools and schools with magnet programs. Private schools do not earn school grades. Know Your Florida School includes all schools earning a grade for the 2015-2016 school year. If your school is a public school but you do not see it listed, here are some of the reasons it may not have earned a grade this year:\r\n<ul>\r\n 	<li>Less than 95 percent of students were assessed.</li>\r\n 	<li>Too few students enrolled.</li>\r\n 	<li>The school is an alternative or Exceptional Student Education school.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nVisit the Florida Department of Education’s Florida School Grades website at schoolgrades.fldoe.org for more information or email evalnrpt@fldoe.org for specific questions.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"8. Does the tool comply with new requirements for report cards under the Every Student Succeeds Act (ESSA)?\" accordion_id=\"8--does-the-tool-comply-with-new-requirements-for-report-cards-under-the-every-student-succeeds-act--essa--\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nKnow Your Florida School is being built to align with new ESSA requirements, including a concise, easy-to-read format; a clearly labeled overview section; disaggregated achievement data on each measure; and school ratings. ESSA requirements are still evolving under the federal rule-making process, and Know Your Florida School will be updated when the requirements are finalized and data from the Florida Department of Education becomes available.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"9. Who created the Know Your School Project and Know Your Florida School?\" accordion_id=\"9--who-created-the-know-your-school-project-and-know-your-florida-school--\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe project and prototype builds off of ExcelinEd’s 2014 My School Information Design Challenge, where web and creative design firms from across the country submitted reimagined online school report cards. Collaborative Communications and Social Driver, the winning team, contributed their expertise to the eventual design of Know Your Florida School. In addition, Jacksonville Public Education Fund serves as the community data partner on the project collecting data from the Florida Department of Education and maintaining the database that powers Know Your Florida School.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"10. How was Know Your Florida School built?\" accordion_id=\"10--how-was-know-your-florida-school-built--\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nKnow Your Florida School was designed and built within a content management system called WordPress. The data powering the tool, which comes from the Florida Department of Education, is housed in a virtual database called an API that is maintained by the Jacksonville Public Education Fund. We are publicly sharing the code used to build Know Your Florida School so other programmers, designers and developers are able to explore how to use this code to set up powerful online school report cards for other states.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [/spb_accordion] [spb_blank_spacer height=\"30\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [spb_text_block title=\"About Know Your Florida School\" animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"][/spb_text_block] [spb_accordion width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"11. What is the Know Your School Project? \" accordion_id=\"11--what-is-the-know-your-school-project---\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nExcelinEd’s Know Your School Project is a resource for states across the nation, highlighting strategies for providing comprehensive accountability data and school-based information that empowers, informs and engages parents and community members.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"12. What will the Know Your School Project achieve?\" accordion_id=\"12--what-will-the-know-your-school-project-achieve-\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe goal of the project is to provide states with a framework to display student achievement and school accountability data in a way that allows parents easy access to understandable data about the effectiveness of their child’s school. Through the Know Your School Project and Know Your Florida School prototype tool, we will provide families and community members with valuable information to encourage engagement with school leaders about the effectiveness of education their child receives.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"13. Why is the Know Your School Project happening now?\" accordion_id=\"13--why-is-the-know-your-school-project-happening-now--\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nThe recently passed Every Student’s Succeeds Act (ESSA) reaffirms and strengthens a focus on state-designed accountability systems and transparent public reporting. A key goal of the Know Your School Project is to support states in successfully developing accessible and useful parent-friendly online report cards. The Know Your School Project represents the culmination of ExcelinEd’s 2014 My School Information Design Challenge.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [spb_accordion_tab title=\"14. How are policymakers and community members in other states involved?\" accordion_id=\"14--how-are-policymakers-and-community-members-in-other-states-involved-\" icon=\"\"] [spb_text_block animation=\"none\" animation_delay=\"0\" padding_vertical=\"0\" padding_horizontal=\"0\" width=\"1/1\" el_position=\"first last\"]\r\n\r\nExcelinEd meets regularly with state leaders from across the nation, and will engage with policymakers and advocates around this project at conferences and convenings over the next year. We will also feature the Know Your School Project at ExcelinEd’s annual National Summit on Education Reform.\r\n\r\n[/spb_text_block] [/spb_accordion_tab] [/spb_accordion] [/spb_row]', 'Frequently Asked Questions', '', 'publish', 'closed', 'closed', '', 'faqs', '', '', '2016-09-20 18:14:47', '2016-09-20 18:14:47', '', 49, 'http://eeflrc.wpengine.com/?page_id=112', 0, 'page', '', 0),
